   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER SIX TO BUILD UP THE BODY OF CHRIST</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>BY GROWING INTO HIM,</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>THE HEAD, IN ALL THINGS Scripture Reading: Eph 4:15-16 OUTLINE The Body of Christ is: The center, reality, and goal of the eternal economy of God, consummating in the New Jerusalem Rev 21:1 22:5.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>The church: The congregation of God's called-out ones.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Appearing in many cities to be the local churches as the many local expressions of the one church on the earth, without any division of nationalities, races, and social ranks Acts 8:1; 13:1; Rev 1:11.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Although the local churches being the many local expressions, they still remain "the one church" Eph 1:22-23 , "the unique church of God" 1 Cor 10:32; Acts 20:28 universally in its unique unity, unique oneness.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>The organism of the processed and consummated Triune God constituted with: The believers in Christ, the many God-men, as the outward human framework.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>The life-giving Spirit, the compound Spirit, as the divine essence.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>The all-inclusive Christ, the unlimited Christ, as the divine element.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>God the Father, who is over all and through all and in all, as the divine source Eph 4:4-6.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>The wife of the processed and consummated Christ: Christ's counterpart, typified by Eve as the counterpart to Adam Gen 2:21b-24; Eph 5:29-33; Rev 21:2, 9; 22:17a: Produced out of Christ through His death and resurrection.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>Joined back to Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>To be one entity with Christ in life and in nature.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>The new man Col 3:10-11; Eph 2:15; 4:24: The corporate God-man: The first God-man, the firstborn Son of God, being the Head of this corporate God-man the new man.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>The many God-men, the many sons of God, being the Body of this corporate God-man the new man.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>Both the Head and the Body of this new man being in resurrection: The first God-man, Christ, becoming the Head of the corporate new man in resurrection, in which He became the Firstborn from the dead Col 1:18.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>The many God-men, the believers in Christ, becoming the Body of the corporate new man in resurrection, in which they, the natural men in race, in religion, in culture, and in social rank, became the regenerated sons of God 1 Pet 1:3a.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>The new creation of God Gal 6:15: The believers in Christ, the corporate new man, the aggregate of the many God-men.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>In Christ 2 Cor 5:17.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>In the resurrection of Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>Through the death of Christ Eph 2:15.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>The processed and consummated Triune God consummating a new creation, out of His old creation, with Himself as the creating element.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>The household of God Eph 2:19b: The household of the faith the universal family of God Gal 6:10 , composed of: God as the Father.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>And the believers in Christ, the many sons of God.</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>To be the manifestation of God in the flesh 1 Tim 3:15-16.</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>The mingling of divinity with humanity: The processed and consummated Triune God mingled with the regenerated and transformed tripartite men.</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>God abiding in man and man abiding in God, coinhering and living as one person John 15:4-5.</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>The two entities becoming one, with their own respective natures remaining distinct.</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>Without a third nature produced.</S>
   <S PAR='30' RSNT='1' SNO='30'>The masterpiece of God Eph 2:10: Created in Christ: Through His death and resurrection.</S>
   <S PAR='31' RSNT='1' SNO='31'>With His divine element in its all-inclusiveness.</S>
   <S PAR='32' RSNT='1' SNO='32'>To walk in the things prepared by God for the accomplishment of His eternal economy.</S>
   <S PAR='33' RSNT='1' SNO='33'>To build up such a Body of Christ Eph 4:12, 16: By growing in life Eph 4:15: Into Christ, the Head.</S>
   <S PAR='34' RSNT='1' SNO='34'>In all things.</S>
   <S PAR='35' RSNT='1' SNO='35'>This growing being the living of a life conformed to the death of Christ by the power of His resurrection and by the bountiful supply of the Spirit of Jesus Christ Phil 3:10; 1:19b.</S>
   <S PAR='36' RSNT='1' SNO='36'>Such a growing affording a corporate building to the Body of Christ Eph 4:16: Joined together through every joint of the rich supply.</S>
   <S PAR='37' RSNT='1' SNO='37'>And knit together through the operation in the measure of each one part.</S>
   </TEXT>
